    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with tin foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-smoky-beef-and-chorizo-pie-with-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced beef</strong> and <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until nicely browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-smoky-beef-and-chorizo-pie-with-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potato[es] </strong>(skin on) into small, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into thin wedges</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-smoky-beef-and-chorizo-pie-with-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef and chorizo are nicely browned, add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>onion wedges</strong>, <strong>chopped potato</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to the dish</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong>, 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[680ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> </p><p>Stir and bring to the boil, then cover with a lid and put in the oven for 50-55 min or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> smoky beef & chorizo</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-smoky-beef-and-chorizo-pie-with-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything's been in the oven for 30 min, dust your work surface with a sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Roll out your<strong> puff pastry</strong> to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and add to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray[s]</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Score a cross in the middle of the pastry and put it in the oven for 15-17 min or until puffed up, golden and cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>pie lid</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-smoky-beef-and-chorizo-pie-with-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-smoky-beef-and-chorizo-pie-with-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Once the <strong>smoky beef & chorizo</strong> is tender, remove the dish from the oven and leave to stand for 5 min with the lid on before serving (this helps the flavours to develop)</p><p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-smoky-beef-and-chorizo-pie-with-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky beef & chorizo</strong> topped with the <strong>pie lid</strong> and the<strong> refreshed peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> </strong>refreshed peas with a little <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
